page.title: 03RIVER ECOLOGY APPLETON WISKE
page.content: were seen.The only other fish noted was the spine loach.The only waterbird was the moorhen.There are many insects flying above the water.The commonest being the midge.Midge larvae or bloodworm were also seen and black and brown leeches.Small water creatures are also plentiful.The most common tree along the river bank is the Hawthorne,but the white willow is also present.Plants noted included Great willow herb,common sorrel,Marsh Marigold,Cow parsley,Red Campion, Nettles and Thistles.
